SlyTitan drops Teammates "TheHeuman" and "Srgt. Buttercups" from Team Titan, Citing Skill Gap and Personal Frustration

Trolly Boy

December 25, 2023
#Game Changers

TORA Esports may have been right about SlyTitan's ego afterall

Team Titan owner SlyTitan has sparked controversy by booting his teammates, "TheHeuman" and "Srgt. Buttercups," from the Apex Legends PSQ #2 tournament. SlyTitan's decision stems from his frustration with their performance and his belief that he cannot carry them past the third round. This incident has generated debate within the gaming community, raising questions about egos, teamwork, and leadership in esports.

SlyTitan, previously known for clashes within his former team due to his egotistical behavior, finds himself once again under scrutiny. Reports suggest that his inflated self-perception and a tendency to prioritize personal glory led to his departure from his previous team. This background highlights a concerning pattern that has now resurfaced in his latest team, Team Titan.

Amidst the Apex Legends PSQ #2 tournament, SlyTitan grew increasingly frustrated with TheHeuman and Srgt. Buttercups' performances. In a moment of dismay, he publicly expressed his disapproval and ultimately decided to remove them from the team. The incident has ignited a heated discussion among fans, with divided opinions on the matter.

While disparities in skill are not uncommon among esports teams, it is rare for team owners to openly denounce their teammates in such a harsh manner. SlyTitan's comments indicate a lack of appreciation for the value of teamwork and could potentially harm morale within the gaming community.

Success in professional gaming hinges not only on individual skill but also on the ability to work cohesively as a team. SlyTitan's decision to dismiss his teammates raises doubts about his leadership capabilities and his understanding of the importance of fostering a positive team dynamic.

As the fallout from this incident unfolds, Team Titan's future remains uncertain. The actions and remarks from SlyTitan have prompted discussions about promoting sportsmanship, constructive collaboration, and personal growth within esports organizations. Moving forward, it is crucial for both players and team owners to prioritize professionalism, respect, and a collective pursuit of success.

In conclusion, SlyTitan's removal of teammates, TheHeuman and Srgt. Buttercups, from the Apex Legends PSQ #2 tournament has ignited controversy within the gaming community. The incident sheds light on the challenges of ego-driven actions, the significance of teamwork, and the need for leadership that promotes a positive team environment. Esports organizations must emphasize sportsmanship, respect, and growth to ensure the long-term success and well-being of their teams.

VCT Game Changers Championship 2023 drops and how to earn them

Brandon Moore

November 27, 2023
#Game Changers

For those tuning in to the VCT Game Changers Championship 2023, there are two drops you can earn to redeem in-game accessories.

The VCT Game Changers Championship 2023 has plenty in store for those watching. There's loads of VALORANT action, a preview of a new Team Deathmatch map, and much more. This includes the ability to earn Game Changers Championship drops if you tune in at certain times.

VCT Game Changers 2023 broadcast talent deliver their predictions for the event

Broadcast talent for the 2023 VCT Game Changers Championship have issued several predictions for the tournament.

Brandon Moore

November 27, 2023

How to earn VCT Game Changers Championship 2023 drops

There are two drops you can earn while tuned in to the VCT Game Changers Championship 2023. These can be earned on both YouTube and Twitch. So, no matter where you're watching the tournament, you can earn in-game rewards.

Continue reading after this ad

Louder Title

(Image via Riot Games)
  • Watch a live game between November 28 and December 2

Essentially, you need to watch a single live match on any day other than the final day. Turn on notifications so you know exactly when the VCT Game Changers Championship goes live, allowing you to watch and earn the Louder Title to display in VALORANT.

Game Changers Trophy Gun Buddy

(Image via Riot Games)
  • Watch a live game on December 3

Continue reading after this ad

December 3 is the last day of the VCT Game Changers Championship 2023. The Grand Final best-of-five series will determine who takes home the trophy. Simply watch the Grand Final and you can earn a trophy of your own, with the GC Championship Trophy Gun Buddy drop.

How to link your account for Game Changers drops

There are a few steps you need to take to ensure you can obtain the VCT Game Changers drops. Thankfully, Riot Games has provided easy-to-follow guides on how to do so for both your Twitch and YouTube accounts:

  • Twitch
  • YouTube

Just take their word for it and you can connect your accounts. Doing so will make it so the drops are automatically triggered when you've watched for the appropriate amount of time. Then you'll just have to redeem them to your VALORANT account. Good luck, have fun!

“Not just popping off and shooting back,” meL on SR’s dominant start at GC Champs 2023

Brandon Moore

November 30, 2023
#Game Changers

Shopify Rebellion’s in-game leader says teamwork, while not trying to just pop off and shoot back, is to credit for team’s early success.

Shopify Rebellion has been decimating the competition at VCT Game Changers Championship 2023. With Melanie "meL" Capone as the IGL, SR has been off to the hottest start we've seen in international VALORANT. Breaking records and breaking hearts. So, we got her take on what's working thus far.

SR meL credits teamwork and practice for solid start in Brazil

(Photo by Adela Sznajder/Riot Games)

Across two series, Shopify Rebellion has only dropped 10 rounds. Two of the world's top Game Changers teams could not secure enough rounds combined to equal a single map victory. That's quite the accomplishment from meL and company.

Continue reading after this ad

After their Upper Semifinals trouncing of BBL Queens, the team took part in a post-match press conference. We were curious as to what's been clicking to deliver such results. We asked meL to let us know what she attributes to the team's incredible opening to the tournament.

"I think for us, the big focus in practice has been comms and adapting on the fly. Just having good teamwork and team play, not just popping off and shooting back. A couple teams in this tournament only tend to do the latter. We've done so much practice and put in a lot of hard work for that first part. That's how it manifests in games, and in matches, our comms have been really good so far. We hope to continue that."

A solid mix of team appreciation and criticism of the opposition in her response. We'll see if things continue to just go right for meL and Shopify Rebellion. Up next for them is defending champions G2 Gozen in the Upper Final. That one is the match we've all been waiting for.

VCT Game Changers 2023 broadcast talent deliver their predictions for the event

Brandon Moore

November 27, 2023
#Game Changers

Broadcast talent for the 2023 VCT Game Changers Championship have issued several predictions for the tournament.

The 2023 VALORANT Champions Tour still has one major event left. That is the Game Changers Championship. Eight teams are converging on São Paulo, Brazil to determine the best in the world. And with that comes an all-star lineup of broadcast talent who have made their predictions for the tournament.

Broadcast talent predictions for VCT Game Changers Championship 2023

(Image via VALORANT Esports)

The talent were given a slew of categories to think about. Each one more than likely thought long and hard about their answers, and have chosen who they think will best represent each question asked. Here are the predictions:

Continue reading after this ad

Who will win Game Changers Championship?

Everyone is on the same page with this particular Game Changers Championship prediction. Everyone polled firmly believes Shopify Rebellion is running away with the trophy.

  • Doug: Shopify Rebellion
  • Athxna: Shopify Rebellion
  • Vansilli: Shopify Rebellion
  • Potter: Shopify Rebellion
  • Aevilcat: Shopify Rebellion
  • Ender: Shopify Rebellion

Most likely to be eliminated without winning a map

There's some split answers here, but the majority believe that Chao Hui EDward Gaming are the most unproven, assuming they will be eliminated outright without winning a map.

  • Doug: KRÜ BLAZE
  • Athxna: Chao Hui EDward Gaming
  • Vansilli: Chao Hui EDward Gaming
  • Potter: Evil Geniuses
  • Aevilcat: Chao Hui EDward Gaming
  • Ender: Chao Hui EDward Gaming

Continue reading after this ad

MVP of Game Changers Championship

The consensus is that florescent is taking the Most Valuable Player. Others chosen include bstrdd and alexis.

  • Doug: florescent
  • Athxna: bstrdd
  • Vansilli: florescent
  • Potter: florescent
  • Aevilcat: florescent
  • Ender: alexis

Will Iso be played in this tournament?

Iso will officially be legally when the Game Changers Championship begins. Will we see him in tournament play? The broadcast talent predictions are right down the middle with this one.

  • Doug: Yes
  • Athxna: Yes
  • Vansilli: Yes
  • Potter: No
  • Aevilcat: No
  • Ender: No

Who's the dark horse of Game Changers Championship?

The final prediction the talent was asked to make asks for a dark horse team for the Game Changers Championship tournament. It could truly be anyone's game when the matches start, but we've got a variety of choices here. The most selected are Team Liquid and Team SMG.

  • Doug: Team Liquid
  • Athxna: Team SMG
  • Vansilli: KRÜ BLAZE
  • Potter: BBL Queens
  • Aevilcat: Team Liquid
  • Ender: Team SMG
